                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 9.769,
                                "byte_start": 92952,
                                "byte_stop": 132031,
                                "text": "The second case, I have to announce is No. 98-1768, Buckman Co. versus the Plaintiffs\u0027 Legal Committee."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 9.769,
                                "stop": 18.742,
                                "byte_start": 132031,
                                "byte_stop": 167976,
                                "text": "Here the respondent represents plaintiffs who claimed injuries resulting from the use of orthopedic bone\u2019s screws in the pedicles of their spines."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.742,
                                "stop": 28.094,
                                "byte_start": 167976,
                                "byte_stop": 205383,
                                "text": "Petitioner is a consulting company that assisted the screws\u0027 manufacturer in navigating the federal regulatory process for these devices."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.094,
                                "stop": 43.12,
                                "byte_start": 205383,
                                "byte_stop": 265465,
                                "text": "The plaintiffs\u2019 claim the petitioner statement to the Food and Drug Administration or FDA as to the intended use of the use of these screws fraudulently induced the FDA to give market approval and ultimately led to plaintiffs\u2019 injuries."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 43.12,
                                "stop": 66.654,
                                "byte_start": 265465,
                                "byte_stop": 359610,
                                "text": "The District Court concluded that these State law so-called fraud on the FDA claims were improper under the Medical Device Amendments to the Federal Food, Drug And Cosmetic Acts or the MDA, but the Court of Appeals for the Third Circuit reversed that decision, saying that there was no express or implied conflict between the plaintiffs\u2019 claims and the MDA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 66.654,
                                "stop": 70.909,
                                "byte_start": 359610,
                                "byte_stop": 376642,
                                "text": "In an opinion filed with the Clerk of the Court today, we reverse."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 70.909,
                                "stop": 81.762,
                                "byte_start": 376642,
                                "byte_stop": 420005,
                                "text": "Under the Supremacy Clause United States Constitution, State law claims have conflict with the federal statute are invalid under what is known as the implied preemption doctrine."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 81.762,
                                "stop": 89.357,
                                "byte_start": 420005,
                                "byte_stop": 450412,
                                "text": "The plaintiffs fraud on the FDA claims create such a conflict with the regulatory regime established by the MDA."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 89.357,
                                "stop": 103.049,
                                "byte_start": 450412,
                                "byte_stop": 505164,
                                "text": "The bones screws at issue here were introduced under a provision of the MDA, directing the FDA to approve devices that it determines, are substantially equivalent to a device that is already on the market."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.049,
                                "stop": 118.488,
                                "byte_start": 505164,
                                "byte_stop": 566918,
                                "text": "Referred to as the 510(k) process, this exception to the FDA\u2019s more time consuming in normal processes prevents unnecessary delay in the development of competition among medical device manufactures."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 118.488,
                                "stop": 125.853,
                                "byte_start": 566918,
                                "byte_stop": 596384,
                                "text": "The 510(k) process sets forth a comprehensive scheme for deciding whether an applicant\u2019s device qualifies."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 125.853,
                                "stop": 133.575,
                                "byte_start": 596384,
                                "byte_stop": 627313,
                                "text": "The process also includes various provisions aimed at detecting, deterring, and punishing false statements."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.575,
                                "stop": 161.973,
                                "byte_start": 627313,
                                "byte_stop": 740893,
                                "text": "The statute makes clear that it is the FDA\u2019s responsibility not that of private litigants to issue a measured response to incidence of non-compliance. The FDA is charged with achieving a variety of difficult and often competing statutory objectives and it would inevitably forth that task if plaintiffs at each of the 50 states, were able to bootstraps state tort claims under the federal regulatory regime."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 161.973,
                                "stop": 173.905,
                                "byte_start": 740893,
                                "byte_stop": 788645,
                                "text": "Both manufacture\u2019s willingness to participate in the approval process and their conduct within that regime would be skewed by fears of unpredictable state litigation."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.905,
                                "stop": 179.603,
                                "byte_start": 788645,
                                "byte_stop": 811424,
                                "text": "This would interfere with the FDA\u2019s own judgment is to how best to achieve the statute\u2019s goal."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 179.603,
                                "stop": 187.606,
                                "byte_start": 811424,
                                "byte_stop": 843398,
                                "text": "The conflict between the MDA and plaintiffs\u2019 fraud on the FDA claims dictates that the latter are impliedly preempted."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 187.606,
                                "stop": 192.314,
                                "byte_start": 843398,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Stevens has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment in which Justice Thomas joins."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
